By vivian Ibobo Lagos – An Ikeja Magistrates’ Court on Tuesday orderedthe remand of a 28-year-old man in prison over alleged rape of a 14-year-old girl. The Chief Magistrate, Mr P.E. Nwaka, ordered that the defendant be remanded in KirikiriPrisons, Lagos, pending advice from the Lagos State Director of Public Prosecutions. The defendant, whose house address was not provided, was arraigned on a two-countcharge of alleged rape and impersonation. The Prosecutor, Insp. Christopher John, said that the defendant committed the offences onOct.1 at his residence. John further told the court that at about 11 p.m. on the same date, the defendant sexuallyassaulted the 14-year-old-girl. He added that “the defendant also claimed to be a member of the Anti-kidnapping personnelof the Nigerian Police Force, a presentation he knew was false.” The prosecutor said that the offence contravened the provisions of sections 260 and 77 of theCriminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Section 260 stipulates life imprisonment on conviction,while Section 77 prescribes three years jail term for impersonating any member of the armed forces. The chief magistrate, who did not take the plea of the defendant, adjourned the case until Nov. 18for mention.